<p><a name="Setting" id="Setting"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Rifts_(role-playing_game)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Setting">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Setting</span></h2>
<table class="metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-content" style="">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image">
<div style="width: 52px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Ambox_content.png" class="image" title="Ambox content.png"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/f/f4/Ambox_content.png" width="40" height="40" border="0" /></a></div>
</td>
<td class="mbox-text" style="">This article <b>describes a work or element of fiction in a primarily <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style_(writing_about_fiction)" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style (writing about fiction)">in-universe</a> style</b>. Please <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Rifts_(role-playing_game)&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Rifts_(role-playing_game)&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow">help rewrite it</a> to <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style_(writing_about_fiction)" title="Wikipedia:Manual of Style (writing about fiction)">explain the fiction more clearly and provide non-fictional perspective</a>.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<table class="metadata plainlinks ambox ambox-style" style="">
<tr>
<td class="mbox-image">
<div style="width: 52px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Ambox_style.png" class="image" title="Ambox style.png"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/d6/Ambox_style.png" width="40" height="40" border="0" /></a></div>
